1543→The identification with $W$ and $Z$ is motivated by their
1544→$SU(2)$ quantum numbers ($s = 1/2$ maps to the doublet structure of $W$,
1545→$s = 1$ to the triplet).  Then
1546→\begin{equation}
1547→R = 1 - \frac{x_+(1/2)}{x_+(1)}
1548→  = \frac{(\sqrt{19} - 3)(\sqrt{19} - \sqrt{3}\,)}{16}
1549→  \;\approx\; 0.2231013\ldots
1550→\end{equation}
1551→The factored form follows from the discriminants of
1552→\eqref{eq:casimir_quartic}: $57 = 3 \times 19$ at $s = 1/2$ and
1553→$12 = 4 \times 3$ at $s = 1$.  Rationalizing the denominator
1554→$\sqrt{3} - 1$ yields an expression in $\sqrt{19}$ and $\sqrt{3}$
1555→alone, which coincides term-by-term with the form found
1556→empirically by de~Vries.
