1558→This should be compared with the on-shell electroweak mixing
1559→parameter:
1560→\begin{equation}
1561→\label{eq:sin2_onshell}
1562→\sin^2\!\theta_W^{\text{os}}
1563→  \;\equiv\; 1 - \frac{M_W^2}{M_Z^2}
1564→  = 0.22320 \pm 0.00026\,,
1565→\end{equation}
1566→using $M_Z = 91.1876 \pm 0.0021\GeV$ and
1567→$M_W = 80.369 \pm 0.013\GeV$ (PDG~2024).
