1569→Since $R = 1 - x_+(1/2)/x_+(1)$ and
1570→$\sin^2\!\theta_W = 1 - M_W^2/M_Z^2$, the two expressions are
1571→\emph{algebraically identical} once one identifies
1572→$x_+(s) = M^2(s)/m^2$.  The prediction $R \approx
1573→\sin^2\!\theta_W$ and the $W$-mass prediction derived below are
1574→therefore \textbf{one and the same observation}, not two
1575→independent tests.
