1577→\paragraph{$W$-mass prediction.}
1578→From $M_W = M_Z\sqrt{1 - R}$:
1579→\begin{equation}
1580→M_W^{\text{pred}}
1581→  = 91.1876 \times \sqrt{1 - 0.22310}
1582→  = 80.374 \pm 0.002\GeV\,,
1583→\end{equation}
1584→which lies $0.39\sigma$ from the PDG average
1585→$M_W = 80.369 \pm 0.013\GeV$ and strongly disfavors the
1586→anomalous CDF-II measurement $M_W^{\text{CDF}} = 80.4335 \pm
1587→0.0094\GeV$ (6.2$\sigma$ tension with $R$).
